= Schleicher and the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span>

The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span>, a veterans' and paramilitary organization that shares much of Schleicher's worldview and commands his respect, has long been courted by the chancellor for cooperation with the Reichswehr. To this end, Schleicher plans to subsidize the organization with state funds, gradually making it dependent on the state and available for use. Still, the general is irritated that its military exercises often overshadow the numerically inferior Reichswehr.

Despite their shared views, <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span> leaders Franz Seldte and Theodor Duesterberg remain wary of Schleicher’s encroachments on their independence. But with the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> now folded into the <span style="color: #BFC8CC;">**DNEF**</span>, the organization finds itself politically isolated, as even its rank-and-file begin to drift into subordination.

