Subordination is the last thing a self-proud veterans' organization like the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span> would accept—but attempts by its leaders to resist have only backfired. At a leadership conference between national and local chapters, they conceded that the era of paramilitaries and political maneuvering is over, and agreed to align the organization with the state in service of the national interest.

In return, the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span> is granted official status as a veterans' association, while sympathetic leaders are rewarded with government posts. Many of its seasoned fighters and officers are absorbed into the Reichswehr, where they will be tasked with training the next generation of recruits.